  "texts": [
    "The flux ratio in the narrow lines will be the closest to M due to the large size of the NLR.",
    "It is important to realise that an accurate measurement of M based on the narrow lines (when unresolved by strong lensing) cannot be achieved by simply looking at the spectral ratios due to the presence of both continuum and line flux at the same wavelength.",
    "Instead, it should be based on the integrated flux in the lines, i.e.",
    "after continuum subtraction [see panel (e) of Fig. 19 ].",
    "In order to better characterise the potential role of variability, one can also compare flux ratios of the same lensed images at multiple epochs."
